{"PATH":[{"def":"A trodden way; a footway.","pos":""},{"def":"A way, course, or track, in which anything moves or has moved; route; passage; an established way; as, the path of a meteor, of a caravan, of a storm, of a pestilence.","pos":""}],"PATHEMATIC":[{"def":"Of, pertaining to, or designating, emotion or suffering.","pos":""}],"PATHETIC":[{"def":"Expressing or showing anger; passionate.","pos":""},{"def":"Affecting or moving the tender emotions, esp.","pos":""}],"PATHFINDER":[{"def":"One who discovers a way or path; one who explores untraversed regions.","pos":""}],"PATHIC":[{"def":"A male who submits to the crime against nature; a catamite.","pos":""}],"PATHLESS":[{"def":"Having no beaten path or way; untrodden; impenetrable; as, pathless woods.","pos":""}],"PATHMAKER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, makes a way or path.","pos":""}],"PATHOGENE":[{"def":"One of a class of virulent microörganisms or bacteria found in the tissues and fluids in infectious diseases, and supposed to be the cause of the disease; a pathogenic organism; a pathogenic bacterium; -- opposed to zymogene.","pos":""}],"PATHOGENIC":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to pathogeny; producting disease; as, a pathogenic organism; a pathogenic bacterium.","pos":""}],"PATHOGNOMONIC":[{"def":"Specially or decisively characteristic of a disease; indicating with certainty a disease; as, a pathognomonic symptom.","pos":""}],"PATHOGNOMY":[{"def":"Expression of the passions; the science of the signs by which human passions are indicated.","pos":""},{"def":"Of or pertaining to pathology.","pos":""}],"PATHOLOGIST":[{"def":"One skilled in pathology; an investigator in pathology; as, the pathologist of a hospital, whose duty it is to determine the causes of the diseases.","pos":""}],"PATHOLOGY":[{"def":"The science which treats of diseases, their nature, causes, progress, symptoms, etc.","pos":""}],"PATHOPOELA":[{"def":"A speech, or figure of speech, designed to move the passion.","pos":""}],"PATHOS":[{"def":"That quality or property of anything which touches the feelings or excites emotions and passions, esp.","pos":""}],"PATHWAY":[{"def":"A footpath; a beaten track; any path or course.","pos":""}]}